cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about Single Image Super-Resolution (SISR), which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new model that combines Residual Learning and Convolutional Sparse Coding, which involves machine learning techniques such as deep learning and sparse coding. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also evaluates the proposed method on benchmark datasets, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses recursive learning, which is a type of neural network architecture, and hence cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible sub-category.
